"{\"uid\": \"abc.net.au-news-2024-04-17-olympic-uniforms-of-the-past-103733684\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Personalise the news and  stay in the know  Emergency  Backstory  Newsletters  \\u4e2d\\u6587\\u65b0\\u95fb  BERITA BAHASA INDONESIA  TOK PISIN  Find any issues using dark mode?Please let us know  By Georgie Hewson  Topic:Olympic Games  Members of the Australian Olympic team display their opening ceremony uniforms for the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 92, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BAHASA INDONESIA\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 228, \"end\": 251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.192319043767075e-21, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Blending the fashion of the time, functionality and elements of national pride, Australia's Olympic Games opening ceremony uniforms capture moments in time.\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.040576730746449e-13, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The outfits that Australia's Olympians will wear into the opening ceremony of the Paris Games in July have been unveiled.\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 489, \"end\": 498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.040576730746449e-13, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each time, the unveiling of the outfits becomes a spectacle of its own, with sport and fashion fans eagerly waiting to see what their country's top athletes will wear as they walk into the main arena.\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 795, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team Australia's outfits for the Paris 2024 Games have been unveiled at Clovelly in Sydney Wednesday morning.\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 797, \"end\": 811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_Australia\", \"score\": 0.9953687646934384, \"rank\": 0.004652783441455672, \"text\": \"Team Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 869, \"end\": 877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clovelly\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.010163705309963e-12, \"text\": \"Clovelly\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clovelly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clovelly\"}, {\"begin\": 881, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.874400607265266e-13, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competition uniformswere revealed earlier this year.\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The emphasis on fashion will be greater than ever this year, as Olympians head to the fashion capital of the world.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1077, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With a global television audience of more than one billion people watching the Opening Ceremony, the Australian Team will wear a uniform inspired by the unmistakable essence of Paris, with fashion at the forefront,\\\" a statement read.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1159, \"end\": 1175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999752975595332, \"rank\": 2.3666988092756416e-05, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 1181, \"end\": 1196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_2016_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 0.999999847751508, \"rank\": 1.5224866746017483e-07, \"text\": \"Australian Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_2016_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_2016_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1257, \"end\": 1262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.4811604815968505e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the 10th time Australian brand Sportscraft has designed the outfits, and Dunlop Volleys are returning as the official shoe.\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1334, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999880321745346, \"rank\": 1.1967968633719841e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1393, \"end\": 1399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunlop_Rubber\", \"score\": 0.9993113265446287, \"rank\": 0.0006724783969511187, \"text\": \"Dunlop\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunlop_Rubber\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunlop_Rubber\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Undoubtedly, like the years before, the uniforms will draw mixed opinions.\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are some of the most memorable outfits over the decades.\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2016 uniform was made with lighter fabric to suit the warmer climate in host city Rio.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1670, \"end\": 1673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999889854308979, \"rank\": 1.101469019262882e-05, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2016 Rio Olympics opening ceremony get-up was described by the Olympic Committee at the time as a reflection of \\\"Australian heritage and lifestyle\\\" that was fitting for the climate and \\\"festive spirit of host city Rio\\\".\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2782364321335694e-21, \"text\": \"2016 Rio Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1793, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999880321745346, \"rank\": 1.1967968633719841e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mint-coloured, stripy, seersucker cotton blazers were the main feature of the ensemble, which included a unique lining inside the jacket bearing each athlete's name.\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 2070, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a lighter, fresh update, giving off preppy, nautical, vibes with white bottoms and boat shoes to finish off the look.\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was met with mixed reviews at the time, with fashion publication GQ writing the outfit was similar to what a \\\"standard issue yacht crew\\\" might wear.\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia, led out by James Tomkins in 2008, ditched the classic green and gold colours to go with blue instead during the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2351, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.040576730746449e-13, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 2373, \"end\": 2386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Tomkins_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.7485107756553062, \"rank\": 0.3337889557136649, \"text\": \"James Tomkins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Tomkins_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Tomkins_(rower)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Getty Images: Cameron Spencer)  While Australia's opening ceremony uniforms have consistently featured green and gold hues at the past few games, it has not always been this way.\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2506, \"end\": 2521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_General_Hospital\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cameron Spencer\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_General_Hospital\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_General_Hospital\"}, {\"begin\": 2530, \"end\": 2539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.040576730746449e-13, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2008, the opening ceremony uniform had a significantly blue themed look to it.\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2753, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Led out by champion rower James Tomkins, the Aussie uniform in Beijing saw the athletes wearing a jacket that faded from a dark blue at the bottom all the way to a shiny looking white at the top near the collars.\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2781, \"end\": 2794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Tomkins_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.7485107756553062, \"rank\": 0.3337889557136649, \"text\": \"James Tomkins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Tomkins_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Tomkins_(rower)\"}, {\"begin\": 2818, \"end\": 2825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999982951090696, \"rank\": 1.7048936168427812e-06, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The colour theme continued in the hats the athletes wore as well.\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Designers said they had to meet the challenges of a Los Angeles summer.\", \"from\": 3036, \"to\": 3107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3088, \"end\": 3099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.634720663541003e-16, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(ABC File)  One of Australia's more kitschy uniforms was the yellow, Australian animal\\u00a0top and skirt worn at the opening ceremony of the 1984 Games in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3108, \"end\": 3111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0564008804113592e-13, \"text\": \"ABC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}, {\"begin\": 3126, \"end\": 3135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.040576730746449e-13, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 3176, \"end\": 3186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999880321745346, \"rank\": 1.1967968633719841e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 3258, \"end\": 3269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.634720663541003e-16, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian fashion designer Prue Acton dreamed up the outfit which comprised an Akubra hat with a feather, skirt, top, belt, necklace and shoes.\", \"from\": 3272, \"to\": 3416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3272, \"end\": 3282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999880321745346, \"rank\": 1.1967968633719841e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 3300, \"end\": 3310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prue_Acton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Prue Acton\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prue_Acton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prue_Acton\"}, {\"begin\": 3352, \"end\": 3358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akubra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akubra\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akubra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akubra\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The top featured a mother and baby koala in a tree, and the skirt showed a kangaroo on an Australian landscape.\", \"from\": 3418, \"to\": 3529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3453, \"end\": 3458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koala\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"koala\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koala\"}, {\"begin\": 3508, \"end\": 3518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999880321745346, \"rank\": 1.1967968633719841e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's uniform was a bright yellow blazer with beige chinos and a white shirt also topped off with an Akubra.\", \"from\": 3531, \"to\": 3643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3636, \"end\": 3642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akubra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akubra\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akubra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akubra\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It really can not get more Aussie than that.\", \"from\": 3645, \"to\": 3689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rowing team members and brothers James, Stephen and Geoffrey Stewart in the uniform worn in Athens in 2004.\", \"from\": 3691, \"to\": 3798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3724, \"end\": 3729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"score\": 0.9999998987641499, \"rank\": 1.0099008673737495e-07, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\"}, {\"begin\": 3752, \"end\": 3759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_of_Stuart\", \"score\": 0.9998910949841444, \"rank\": 0.00010884471133460782, \"text\": \"Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_of_Stuart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_of_Stuart\"}, {\"begin\": 3783, \"end\": 3789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9986597938704145, \"rank\": 0.0013420046923407058, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(AAP:\\u00a0Dean Lewins, file photo)  In 2004, the designers of Australia's opening ceremony uniform took a more relaxed, sporty approach.\", \"from\": 3798, \"to\": 3930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3804, \"end\": 3808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\", \"score\": 0.9953823180818424, \"rank\": 0.0046358163379651585, \"text\": \"Dean\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dean_Winchester\"}, {\"begin\": 3856, \"end\": 3865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.040576730746449e-13, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The uniform was also more unisex, with men and women both wearing grey trousers, white shirts and green, star-patterned bomber jackets.\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 4067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's Olympic team enters the Montjuic\\u00a0 Stadium during the opening ceremony of the 1992 Games.\", \"from\": 4069, \"to\": 4169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4069, \"end\": 4078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.040576730746449e-13, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Getty Images: David Madison)  The 1992 Olympic Games in Barcelona featured one of Australia's more flamboyant opening ceremony looks.\", \"from\": 4169, \"to\": 4303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4190, \"end\": 4197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.690786702964295e-20, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}, {\"begin\": 4226, \"end\": 4235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\", \"score\": 0.9999937694204543, \"rank\": 6.230618371409591e-06, \"text\": \"Barcelona\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\"}, {\"begin\": 4252, \"end\": 4261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.040576730746449e-13, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team's men and women each wore a variation of a short-sleeved shirt featuring red, blue, yellow and white Australian wildflowers.\", \"from\": 4305, \"to\": 4438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4415, \"end\": 4425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999880321745346, \"rank\": 1.1967968633719841e-05, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a very popular style at the time, women wore green skorts and sandals while men wore dark green tailored shorts with brown shoes and long socks.\", \"from\": 4440, \"to\": 4587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The look was completed with a wide-brimmed, straw hat.\", \"from\": 4589, \"to\": 4643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The outfits for Tokyo 2020 were inspired by the vibrant colours of the host city.\", \"from\": 4645, \"to\": 4726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4661, \"end\": 4666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9971808873048261, \"rank\": 0.0028261995784945823, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Getty Images: Matt King)  With the humidity of a Tokyo summer in mind, designer Sportscraft's main focus for the 2020 opening ceremony was ensuring the athletes were comfortable.\", \"from\": 4726, \"to\": 4905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4776, \"end\": 4781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9971808873048261, \"rank\": 0.0028261995784945823, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4807, \"end\": 4818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sportscraft\", \"score\": 0.9999999999563443, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sportscraft\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sportscraft\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sportscraft\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The design was inspired by the \\\"electric lights, vibrant colours and bustling atmosphere synonymous with Tokyo\\\".\", \"from\": 4907, \"to\": 5019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5012, \"end\": 5017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9971808873048261, \"rank\": 0.0028261995784945823, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The angles used in the designs were inspired by Japan's famous Shibuya Crossing intersection, along with elements of the Southern Cross.\", \"from\": 5021, \"to\": 5157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5069, \"end\": 5074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999998955095234, \"rank\": 8.525597263373867e-08, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 5084, \"end\": 5100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shibuya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4645501420382438e-19, \"text\": \"Shibuya Crossing\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shibuya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shibuya\"}, {\"begin\": 5142, \"end\": 5156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crux\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8628009703888798e-13, \"text\": \"Southern Cross\", \"types\": [\"Q8928\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Crux\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian team during the opening ceremony of the Sydney 2000 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 5159, \"to\": 5240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5159, \"end\": 5173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.350087774781646e-42, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 5163, \"end\": 5178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999188626167, \"rank\": 8.104008394481088e-08, \"text\": \"Australian team\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_men's_national_rugby_league_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Allsport: Clive Brunskill)  When designing the Australian Olympic team's uniform for the Sydney 2000 opening ceremony, the Woolmark Company and Mambo drew inspiration from Australia's landscape and culture.\", \"from\": 5240, \"to\": 5447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5288, \"end\": 5311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.192319043767075e-21, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5364, \"end\": 5372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woolmark\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Woolmark\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woolmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woolmark\"}, {\"begin\": 5385, \"end\": 5390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mambo_Graphics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.935689960974483e-21, \"text\": \"Mambo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mambo_Graphics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mambo_Graphics\"}, {\"begin\": 5413, \"end\": 5422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.040576730746449e-13, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the median age of the Aussie Olympic team was 22, the designers wanted to make sure the look was youthful.\", \"from\": 5449, \"to\": 5558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The result was an ochre-coloured, cropped jacket, a yellow checked, short-sleeve shirt and a green skirt or pair of pants.\", \"from\": 5560, \"to\": 5682, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The uniform was modified for the closing ceremony to include a Mambo shirt that featured the design, Suburbia, by Lachlan Barbard.\", \"from\": 5684, \"to\": 5814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5747, \"end\": 5752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mambo_Graphics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.935689960974483e-21, \"text\": \"Mambo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mambo_Graphics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mambo_Graphics\"}, {\"begin\": 5785, \"end\": 5793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suburb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1666683349209587e-41, \"text\": \"Suburbia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suburb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suburb\"}, {\"begin\": 5798, \"end\": 5805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_River\", \"score\": 0.9970497511018047, \"rank\": 0.002958978606058022, \"text\": \"Lachlan\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian Olympic team members model the opening ceremony uniform in Sydney.\", \"from\": 5816, \"to\": 5893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5816, \"end\": 5839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.192319043767075e-21, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5886, \"end\": 5892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.874400607265266e-13, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From left to right: Adam Gibson, Naomi Flood, Murray Stewart, Libby Trickett, Kynan Maley, Sarah Tait and Lauren Jackson.\", \"from\": 5894, \"to\": 6015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5914, \"end\": 5925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Gibson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Gibson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Gibson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Gibson\"}, {\"begin\": 5940, \"end\": 5954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murray_Stewart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Murray Stewart\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murray_Stewart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murray_Stewart\"}, {\"begin\": 5956, \"end\": 5970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Libby_Trickett\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Libby Trickett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Libby_Trickett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Libby_Trickett\"}, {\"begin\": 5972, \"end\": 59